The initial estimate of 25 dead in the Columbine High massacre was incorrect due to overlapping counts by SWAT teams.
The death toll was confirmed at 15, including the gunmen.
Rumors of further attacks spread, causing fear.
Chatfield High School reopened, providing support for students.
Pat Buchanan stated that stricter gun laws wouldn't have prevented the tragedy.
The community came together in mourning, with support pouring in from around the world.
The return to classes at Columbine was delayed due to ongoing funerals.
Despite the tragedy, students found solace in sports and community support.
